                    <scopecontent><p>[Hayman regarded her invitations as works of art, with decorated borders, drawings, and calligraphy.  Interestingly, perhaps because she regarded them as artwork, Hayman saved only her own writings to correspondents.  There are no letters or invitations "to D'Arcy Hayman" in the collection. ]</p>
